## Next steps

Import and use in your command handlers:

```ts
import { emit, note, reportError, detectMode } from './agent/json-mode';

program
  .option('--json', 'emit JSON for agents')
  .command('list')
  .action(async (opts) => {
    note('Fetching items...', opts);
    const items = await fetchItems();
    emit(items, opts, (data) => {
      for (const item of data) console.log(`- ${item.name}`);
    });
  });
```

In JSON mode (`--json` or piped stdout): NDJSON to stdout, nothing to stderr.
In human mode (TTY): formatted output to stdout, notes to stderr.

Pairs with `next-steps` block for agent-first CLIs.

## Next steps

```ts
import { emit } from './agent/json-mode';
import { emitNextSteps } from './agent/next-steps';

program.command('list').action(async (opts) => {
  const items = await fetchItems();
  emit(items, opts);
  emitNextSteps([
    { command: 'myapp show <id>', description: 'see details for one item' },
    { command: 'myapp export', description: 'export all', optional: true },
  ], opts);
});
```

Agents parse `stderr` line-by-line and filter `{type: 'next-step', ...}`
objects to know what to try next. Humans see a formatted block with
arrow bullets.

**Note**: the registryDependency on json-mode uses a localhost URL for
dev. In production it will point to https://cligentic.railly.dev/r/json-mode.json.
